about.summary: Bindings for Poisson regression models for use with the 'parsnip' package. Models include simple generalized linear models, Bayesian models, and zero-inflated Poisson models (Zeileis, Kleiber, and Jackman (2008) <doi:10.18637/jss.v027.i08>).

name: r-poissonreg
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.0.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-poissonreg
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/poissonreg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/poissonreg/poissonreg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a97acfe95662a4f12b9ba62fc2e9e4c7574ff56f58926fee44534130899a1113

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-parsnip >=0.1.0
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-parsnip >=0.1.0
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('poissonreg')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('poissonreg')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/tidymodels/poissonreg
  license: MIT
  summary: Bindings for Poisson regression models for use with the 'parsnip' package. Models
    include simple generalized linear models, Bayesian models, and zero-inflated Poisson
    models (Zeileis, Kleiber, and Jackman (2008) <doi:10.18637/jss.v027.i08>).
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Description: Bindings for Poisson regression models for use with the 'parsnip' package. Models include simple generalized linear models, Bayesian models, and zero-inflated Poisson models (Zeileis, Kleiber, and Jackman (2008) <doi:10.18637/jss.v027.i08>).
